1
00:01:04,959 --> 00:01:05,959
It's a rare opportunity.

2
00:01:06,239 --> 00:01:07,159
I must seize it.

3
00:01:15,599 --> 00:01:16,959
Do you really want to buy my internet cafe?

4
00:01:17,480 --> 00:01:18,799
I'm sincere about buying.

5
00:01:18,959 --> 00:01:20,359
Why don't you give me a real price?

6
00:01:20,719 --> 00:01:21,280
Six hundred thousand.

7
00:01:23,159 --> 00:01:24,319
If I had six hundred thousand,

8
00:01:24,319 --> 00:01:25,680
why would I buy an old one?

9
00:01:28,719 --> 00:01:29,519
How about this?

10
00:01:30,040 --> 00:01:32,359
If you can pay the full amount upfront,

11
00:01:32,840 --> 00:01:33,439
five hundred thousand.

12
00:01:37,599 --> 00:01:40,000
I remember that transfer ad of yours.

13
00:01:40,719 --> 00:01:42,159
It seems it's been up for quite a while.

14
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:44,719
Your coffee.

15
00:01:45,560 --> 00:01:46,159
Thanks.

16
00:01:46,319 --> 00:01:46,640
Enjoy.

17
00:01:48,640 --> 00:01:50,079
The only advantage your shop has

18
00:01:50,079 --> 00:01:51,319
is that it's right next to Yunhai University.

19
00:01:51,760 --> 00:01:54,200
Exactly. Isn't that worth five hundred thousand?

20
00:01:54,599 --> 00:01:56,000
The customer base is indeed valuable.

21
00:01:56,480 --> 00:01:57,799
But customers care about the specs,

22
00:01:57,959 --> 00:01:58,760
not the signboard.

23
00:01:59,120 --> 00:02:00,280
I heard that on this street,

24
00:02:00,280 --> 00:02:01,799
a new internet cafe is opening next month.

25
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:03,120
The specs are all top-tier.

26
00:02:03,439 --> 00:02:05,359
If I have to compete with him for customers then,

27
00:02:05,359 --> 00:02:06,599
won't I have to spend a fortune replacing machines?

28
00:02:07,079 --> 00:02:08,000
If you do the math,

29
00:02:08,199 --> 00:02:10,400
I'm afraid it would cost more than opening a new one.

30
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:13,280
If you were me, would you take this deal?

31
00:02:22,120 --> 00:02:23,879
400,000. That's the lowest.

32
00:02:24,960 --> 00:02:26,319
It's already a bargain.

33
00:02:27,479 --> 00:02:29,759
I have to sell DomainNet to get my first pot of gold.

34
00:02:29,759 --> 00:02:31,479
To build my business matrix quickly.

35
00:02:32,039 --> 00:02:33,599
Can you give me a week to consider it?

36
00:02:36,960 --> 00:02:38,879
All right, but I can't wait too long.

37
00:02:39,199 --> 00:02:39,599
No problem.

38
00:02:40,120 --> 00:02:41,639
You can keep looking for buyers in the meantime.

39
00:02:41,800 --> 00:02:43,240
If someone offers a higher price than me,

40
00:02:43,240 --> 00:02:44,159
you can sell it to them anytime.

41
00:02:46,879 --> 00:02:47,680
Waiter.

42
00:02:48,680 --> 00:02:49,759
Let me pay for the coffee.

43
00:02:49,840 --> 00:02:50,719
I really appreciate you giving me

44
00:02:50,719 --> 00:02:51,599
this opportunity to meet.

45
00:02:51,960 --> 00:02:52,800
Once I've made up my mind,

46
00:02:53,039 --> 00:02:54,240
I'll come find you at the cyber cafe right away.

47
00:02:55,719 --> 00:02:56,759
I forgot to ask just now.

48
00:02:57,280 --> 00:02:59,159
What should I call you, young man?

49
00:02:59,360 --> 00:02:59,919
Chen Fan.

50
00:03:00,360 --> 00:03:01,080
Chen, as in "ear" and "east".

51
00:03:01,159 --> 00:03:01,919
Fan, meaning "ordinary".

52
00:03:02,360 --> 00:03:03,639
At your age,

53
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:05,599
to have such insight and experience...

54
00:03:06,080 --> 00:03:07,240
You're certainly no "ordinary" person.

55
00:03:08,319 --> 00:03:09,680
Hello. Tang Meiyun.

56
00:03:11,719 --> 00:03:12,360
Hello, Sister Tang.

57
00:03:13,520 --> 00:03:14,479
No need to be so polite.

58
00:03:15,039 --> 00:03:15,800
I'll be going now.

59
00:03:15,960 --> 00:03:16,719
I'll be waiting for your good news.

60
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:17,360
Sure.

61
00:03:19,319 --> 00:03:19,960
Take care, Sister Tang.

62
00:03:24,400 --> 00:03:25,080
Are you blind?

63
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:26,599
This bone china set costs over a thousand!

64
00:03:26,599 --> 00:03:28,039
How much do you even make in a day?

65
00:03:28,240 --> 00:03:29,120
Do you have no brains?

66
00:03:29,120 --> 00:03:30,439
You clumsy idiot.

67
00:03:30,439 --> 00:03:31,560
You can't even do this simple job right.

68
00:03:31,840 --> 00:03:32,680
I'm docking half a month's wages.

69
00:03:32,919 --> 00:03:33,520
Stop picking them up! Stop it!

70
00:03:35,159 --> 00:03:36,199
Why are you insulting him?

71
00:03:36,479 --> 00:03:37,520
I saw everything from over there.

72
00:03:37,520 --> 00:03:38,879
You didn't mop the floor clean at all.

73
00:03:38,879 --> 00:03:40,000
That's why he slipped.

74
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:40,960
He's working for you here.

75
00:03:40,960 --> 00:03:42,280
You have to ensure the place is safe, right?

76
00:03:42,879 --> 00:03:43,719
Well, yes.

77
00:03:44,360 --> 00:03:45,479
He should pay for the broken cup.

78
00:03:45,719 --> 00:03:46,800
But docking half a month of his wages?

79
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:47,680
Is that reasonable?

80
00:03:47,879 --> 00:03:48,199
Hmph.

81
00:03:49,039 --> 00:03:50,879
That's the rule here.

82
00:03:50,879 --> 00:03:52,319
Or I can call the police right now.

83
00:03:52,319 --> 00:03:53,360
And let them judge who's right.

84
00:03:53,759 --> 00:03:55,199
Him falling here counts as a work injury.

85
00:03:55,199 --> 00:03:56,400
How much should you compensate him?

86
00:03:58,960 --> 00:03:59,599
Just my luck.

87
00:03:59,680 --> 00:04:02,159
Get out! Don't bother coming back tomorrow.

88
00:04:05,080 --> 00:04:06,039
No manners at all.

89
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:10,159
I just got a batch of game cards from the cyber cafe.

90
00:04:10,240 --> 00:04:11,599
How about it? Want some?

91
00:04:11,759 --> 00:04:13,039
I don't want that.

92
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:15,520
Hey, our genius roommate is back.

93
00:04:18,439 --> 00:04:19,480
So it was you.

94
00:04:19,959 --> 00:04:20,759
You two know each other?

95
00:04:21,879 --> 00:04:22,839
Let's introduce ourselves properly.

96
00:04:23,040 --> 00:04:23,800
I'm Chen Fan.

97
00:04:23,879 --> 00:04:24,319
Liang Shichu.

98
00:04:24,800 --> 00:04:26,319
Thanks for what happened this afternoon.

99
00:04:26,319 --> 00:04:27,920
Hey, it was nothing.

100
00:04:28,399 --> 00:04:29,519
But wait, school just started.

101
00:04:29,519 --> 00:04:30,480
Why are you already working part-time?

102
00:04:31,439 --> 00:04:32,360
It's all for this.

103
00:04:33,199 --> 00:04:35,360
When I entered the programming contest,

104
00:04:35,360 --> 00:04:36,360
this was the model I had my eye on.

105
00:04:37,160 --> 00:04:38,720
The specs are good enough to run large games.

106
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:40,040
It's just the price...

107
00:04:40,040 --> 00:04:41,480
It costs three months of my dad's salary.

108
00:04:41,480 --> 00:04:43,399
So I borrowed money to buy it first.

109
00:04:43,560 --> 00:04:45,959
Figured I'd work a few jobs in college to pay it back.

110
00:04:46,160 --> 00:04:47,040
By the way, Fan.

111
00:04:47,319 --> 00:04:49,079
Tell Liang about your DomainNet.

112
00:04:49,879 --> 00:04:51,639
It's just a platform for domain registration

113
00:04:51,639 --> 00:04:52,519
and trading.

114
00:04:52,800 --> 00:04:53,920
Let me show you.

115
00:04:54,480 --> 00:04:55,600
It's really awesome.

116
00:05:02,199 --> 00:05:04,639
This is DomainNet.

117
00:05:07,920 --> 00:05:08,959
That's impossible.

118
00:05:09,639 --> 00:05:11,040
Who on earth is on the other side?

119
00:05:11,560 --> 00:05:12,560
I've been a hacker for so long,

120
00:05:12,959 --> 00:05:14,399
but this is the first time I've met someone this good.

121
00:05:16,560 --> 00:05:19,120
Did you build this website all by yourself?

122
00:05:20,360 --> 00:05:21,839
And I have to maintain it all by myself, too.

123
00:05:22,399 --> 00:05:24,600
I have to promote it and fight off hackers.

124
00:05:24,600 --> 00:05:25,360
It's a real hassle.

125
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:27,600
The backend code and firewall...

126
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:29,000
...you wrote all of that yourself too?

127
00:05:29,360 --> 00:05:30,360
Yeah. Why?

128
00:05:32,160 --> 00:05:32,959
Nothing.

129
00:05:33,120 --> 00:05:35,879
I just think your code logic is really solid.

130
00:05:36,199 --> 00:05:37,879
Supporting a hundred thousand users isn't easy.

131
00:05:38,680 --> 00:05:40,000
Truly worthy of a gold award.

132
00:05:40,240 --> 00:05:42,160
I could tell at a glance your foundation is solid.

133
00:05:42,759 --> 00:05:44,879
So, what are your plans for it later?

134
00:05:46,079 --> 00:05:48,319
I want to wait for a big buyer and sell the site.

135
00:05:48,480 --> 00:05:49,560
Free up time to do other things.

136
00:05:49,959 --> 00:05:50,759
Sell it to whom?

137
00:05:52,040 --> 00:05:54,279
The bigger the platform, the better, of course.

138
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:56,160
Like HiChina, for example.

139
00:05:56,519 --> 00:05:57,800
I thought once the data numbers went up,

140
00:05:57,800 --> 00:05:58,959
someone would definitely come looking.

141
00:05:59,160 --> 00:06:00,720
But months have passed without a word.

142
00:06:01,519 --> 00:06:02,759
I'm thinking I need to be more proactive.

143
00:06:02,759 --> 00:06:03,600
I just haven't figured out how yet.

144
00:06:03,800 --> 00:06:06,000
Maybe I can help you.

145
00:06:06,560 --> 00:06:07,360
You can help me?

146
00:06:09,439 --> 00:06:11,040
I entered a programming contest last year

147
00:06:11,040 --> 00:06:12,240
and met President Ma of HiChina.

148
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:14,839
How about I try contacting him?

149
00:06:18,600 --> 00:06:20,160
That's awesome of you, Brother Liang.

150
00:06:20,240 --> 00:06:21,279
If this works out,

151
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:22,680
I'll buy ten computers to thank you.

152
00:06:23,480 --> 00:06:24,240
Sorry to keep you waiting, President Ma.

153
00:06:25,279 --> 00:06:26,800
I'm Chen Fan, the creator of DomainNet.

154
00:06:27,399 --> 00:06:29,319
I didn't expect you to be so young.

155
00:06:29,560 --> 00:06:30,000
Have a seat.

156
00:06:30,560 --> 00:06:33,360
President Ma, what would you like to eat?

157
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:34,160
Steamed buns.

158
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:35,800
Boss, bring us some steamed buns.

159
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:38,759
Choosing a breakfast stall to talk business...

160
00:06:38,759 --> 00:06:39,720
...that's a first for me.

161
00:06:40,279 --> 00:06:41,319
Regarding DomainNet,

162
00:06:41,720 --> 00:06:42,879
what price is your company prepared to offer?

163
00:06:43,560 --> 00:06:44,240
Five hundred thousand.

164
00:06:45,399 --> 00:06:46,800
Plus we'll hire you to work at HiChina.

165
00:06:47,079 --> 00:06:48,600
You can choose any position.

166
00:06:49,399 --> 00:06:50,319
Thank you for the kind offer, President Ma.

167
00:06:50,319 --> 00:06:51,319
I'll pass on the job.

168
00:06:51,319 --> 00:06:52,600
I only want the acquisition payment.

169
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:54,480
Two million.

170
00:06:55,920 --> 00:06:57,680
That's a bit beyond my expectations.

171
00:07:00,399 --> 00:07:00,920
President Ma,

172
00:07:01,639 --> 00:07:02,959
actually, you're not the only one

173
00:07:02,959 --> 00:07:03,959
interested in acquiring DomainNet.

174
00:07:04,560 --> 00:07:06,519
A company from Guangzhou a few days ago

175
00:07:06,519 --> 00:07:07,639
offered 1.5 million.

176
00:07:07,639 --> 00:07:08,360
I didn't agree.

177
00:07:08,920 --> 00:07:10,920
Because I think HiChina has a stronger brand.

178
00:07:11,399 --> 00:07:13,160
I believe if we work together,

179
00:07:13,199 --> 00:07:16,319
we can definitely make this platform bigger and stronger.

180
00:07:26,199 --> 00:07:28,240
My 100,000 users aren't just numbers.

181
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:29,800
They're the result of me staying up until dawn in internet cafes,

182
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:31,839
typing out code line by line.

183
00:07:32,079 --> 00:07:33,439
Conservatively speaking, right now

184
00:07:33,439 --> 00:07:34,639
we're seeing growth of several hundred users.

185
00:07:35,160 --> 00:07:36,439
Do you think in another three months,

186
00:07:37,079 --> 00:07:38,319
you'll still be able to get it at this price?

187
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:40,040
This acquisition of ours

188
00:07:40,040 --> 00:07:41,759
definitely won't be a one-time deal.

189
00:07:42,399 --> 00:07:44,920
Rest assured, if I have any good ideas in the future,

190
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:46,680
whether it's building a new platform

191
00:07:46,959 --> 00:07:48,759
or developing a new practical business model,

192
00:07:49,360 --> 00:07:50,120
you and HiChina

193
00:07:50,399 --> 00:07:52,680
will be the first partners I seek out.

194
00:07:52,959 --> 00:07:54,519
You really have some tenacity, young man.

195
00:07:54,920 --> 00:07:56,279
You've been chasing me for so many days.

196
00:07:56,920 --> 00:07:59,519
Fine. Two million it is.

197
00:07:59,920 --> 00:08:01,920
What I value is the potential behind it.

198
00:08:03,839 --> 00:08:04,639
Pleasure doing business.

199
00:08:04,920 --> 00:08:05,720
Pleasure doing business.

200
00:08:06,920 --> 00:08:09,399
Ruochu, we've secured our internet cafe.

201
00:08:21,160 --> 00:08:21,680
Here.

202
00:08:22,279 --> 00:08:23,199
For me?

203
00:08:23,839 --> 00:08:24,680
I don't want it.

204
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:27,040
This phone looks really expensive.

205
00:08:27,040 --> 00:08:27,959
Hurry up and return it.

206
00:08:29,199 --> 00:08:31,079
Don't worry, we can afford it.

207
00:08:32,200 --> 00:08:33,120
I sold that website.

208
00:08:33,120 --> 00:08:34,519
This phone was bought with that money.

209
00:08:34,679 --> 00:08:36,080
Really? You sold it?

210
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:36,919
That's great!

211
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:39,480
Let me give you a sneak peek.

212
00:08:39,639 --> 00:08:41,080
I sold that website for two million.

213
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:42,200
I plan to use it to buy an internet cafe.

214
00:08:42,960 --> 00:08:44,159
Put it away, quickly.

215
00:08:45,840 --> 00:08:46,559
Do you remember?

216
00:08:46,559 --> 00:08:48,000
You were the one who found

217
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:49,240
the address for this internet cafe.

218
00:08:49,240 --> 00:08:51,320
No matter what, I have to thank you.

219
00:08:51,759 --> 00:08:53,120
That was all your own doing.

220
00:08:53,120 --> 00:08:54,440
What does it have to do with me?

221
00:08:55,320 --> 00:08:57,679
This is the first gift I've given you.

222
00:08:57,679 --> 00:08:58,679
Just accept it.

223
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:00,240
I spent a long time picking it out.

224
00:09:00,240 --> 00:09:01,320
Do you want me to throw it away?

225
00:09:01,320 --> 00:09:01,799
Hey, hey!

226
00:09:07,720 --> 00:09:09,240
I bought you a phone...

227
00:09:09,279 --> 00:09:10,600
...because I miss you too much.

228
00:09:11,120 --> 00:09:12,639
I want to see you every day.

229
00:09:12,639 --> 00:09:14,360
Contact you, hear your voice.

230
00:09:15,720 --> 00:09:18,440
Calling from outside is really inconvenient.

231
00:09:19,799 --> 00:09:21,320
There are things I'm too shy to say.

232
00:09:23,480 --> 00:09:25,679
What are you too shy to say?

233
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:27,639
Come here.

234
00:09:32,440 --> 00:09:33,879
What nonsense are you saying?

235
00:09:33,879 --> 00:09:34,799
Okay, I won't say it.

236
00:09:35,279 --> 00:09:37,440
Look, I've already installed the SIM card for you.

237
00:09:37,840 --> 00:09:39,000
I saved my number in it too.

238
00:09:42,600 --> 00:09:43,399
Mine.

239
00:09:44,200 --> 00:09:44,679
Hello?

240
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:46,200
Hey, Ruochu.

241
00:09:46,879 --> 00:09:47,799
You have a call.

242
00:09:48,080 --> 00:09:50,080
Hehe, what are you doing?

243
00:09:50,399 --> 00:09:51,399
Have you eaten yet?

244
00:09:51,879 --> 00:09:52,840
I recognize this one.

245
00:09:55,720 --> 00:09:57,240
Why did you buy yourself a cheap one?

246
00:09:57,240 --> 00:09:58,399
And buy me an expensive one?

247
00:09:58,960 --> 00:10:00,559
I said I'd give you the best.

248
00:10:01,919 --> 00:10:02,159
Hey.

249
00:10:02,399 --> 00:10:03,320
I just want this one.

250
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:05,720
I just use it to call you anyway.

251
00:10:05,720 --> 00:10:07,240
What's the difference between expensive and cheap?

252
00:10:07,519 --> 00:10:08,200
No, I...

253
00:10:08,200 --> 00:10:09,879
Say another word and I won't want it at all.

254
00:10:13,399 --> 00:10:15,320
I'll listen, okay?

255
00:10:15,639 --> 00:10:17,320
That's more like it. Let's eat.

256
00:10:21,080 --> 00:10:21,559
Cheers.

257
00:10:29,799 --> 00:10:30,519
Congratulations.

258
00:10:31,120 --> 00:10:32,759
From now on, you're the boss here.

259
00:10:33,200 --> 00:10:34,919
I've left the admin, Little Li, to you.

260
00:10:34,919 --> 00:10:36,960
You can ask him about the basics.

261
00:10:37,120 --> 00:10:38,559
If we want to make this big...

262
00:10:38,639 --> 00:10:39,759
...one person probably isn't enough.

263
00:10:43,440 --> 00:10:45,440
Why don't you be my manager?

264
00:10:46,559 --> 00:10:47,159
Really?

265
00:10:47,159 --> 00:10:48,519
Your family has been in business since you were young.

266
00:10:48,519 --> 00:10:49,639
You must have picked up a lot.

267
00:10:49,639 --> 00:10:50,720
Plus, you're my brother.

268
00:10:51,159 --> 00:10:51,919
I trust you.

269
00:10:52,120 --> 00:10:53,480
But for me to do this...

270
00:10:53,480 --> 00:10:54,840
You come here to surf the web every day anyway.

271
00:10:55,159 --> 00:10:56,120
Just keep an eye on things for me.

272
00:10:58,840 --> 00:10:59,240
Alright.

273
00:10:59,919 --> 00:11:01,600
I'll definitely watch the place for you.

274
00:11:02,159 --> 00:11:03,639
By the way.

275
00:11:03,840 --> 00:11:06,440
Do you want to keep the internet cafe's name?

276
00:11:09,320 --> 00:11:10,919
Boss, do you have any ideas?

